&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Staff Nurse - Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you a newly qualified children’s nurse or an experienced band 5 nurse? Our ward and the children of Croydon need you!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are enthusiastic and motivated about delivering the highest quality nursing care to children and young people, then come and work at Croydon and become a valued member of our team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for Band 5 paediatric nurses to join our friendly team on Rupert Bear ward, with responsibility for providing high quality nursing care to babies, children and young people. Rupert Bear is a sixteen bedded ward providing medical, surgical and oncology care to children and is part of an integrated children’s nursing service across Croydon which also includes a nurse led children’s day surgery unit, children’s emergency department and thriving community team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will provide you with the opportunity to; &lt;br /&gt;• Be supported by experienced children’s nurses and practice education &lt;br /&gt;team through comprehensive induction and preceptorship programmes &lt;br /&gt;to identify and meet your learning needs.&lt;br /&gt;• Enhance your knowledge by working alongside our children’s asthma, &lt;br /&gt;diabetes and oncology nurse specialists&lt;br /&gt;• Work in partnership with the Community Children’s Nurses and Special &lt;br /&gt;School Nursing Team&lt;br /&gt;• Experience in-house simulation courses: Paediatric Retrieval and &lt;br /&gt;Acute Multi-Disciplinary Simulation (PRAMS) and sessions on the ward.&lt;br /&gt;• Develop your mentorship skills &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Training at the Trust also supports nursing revalidation, helping nurses to build their portfolio of CPD evidence and competency documents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should meet the criteria outlined within the job description and specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 5th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSusanne FernandesJob titleward managerTelephone number0208401 3188Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please feel free to contact us for an informal visit or if you have any questions -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Susanne Fernandes, Ward Manager - Rupert Bear Ward 0208 401 3188&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
